                        <div class="profile" >
                            
                                

<img class="author-profile-picture" src="http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/site_furniture/2010/09/01/no-user-image.gif" height="60" width="60" alt="" />
<a href="http://www.guardian.co.uk/discussion/user/idunnosomename" title="User profile page">idunnosomename</a>

                            
                            <p class="date">8 September 2011 7:45AM</p>
                        </div>
                    
					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>I don't care what newspaper recipes keep saying, making pizza bases at home is a pain in the arse, so a few failed attempts meant no pizza ever graced my oven. Marks and Spencer however have finally started doing a nice plain pizza base, which means I can enjoy pizza at home occasionally. Before that the only plain bases it seems you could buy were the Napolina ones that were like a great big biscuit. Why it took so long to sell a good ready-meal quality base with nothing on it is a mystery!</p><p>I made a chili beef pizza with some old left-over frozen tough steak, softened in the tomato sauce with chili and paprika, absolutely wonderful. Other fun to be had - Chicken and Ramiro red pepper, Dolchelatte and courgette. Knowing Marks they'll just stop doing them for no reason soon.</p>
						
					</div>
