                        <div class="profile" >
                            
                                

<img class="author-profile-picture" src="http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/site_furniture/2010/09/01/no-user-image.gif" height="60" width="60" alt="" />
<a href="http://www.guardian.co.uk/discussion/user/Sulis2" title="User profile page">Sulis2</a>

                            
                            <p class="date">8 September 2011 9:18AM</p>
                        </div>
                    
					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>Making pizza at home is so easy I now save a fortune compared to getting them delivered - and the kids prefer them, as they can make the toppings just as they like.</p><p>I use the 00 flour, mixed with the yeast mixture straight in the KitchenAid mixer bowl, with a decent slug of olive oil. Leave for an hour to rise, bash it down again and it can be used straight away. </p><p>I have an AGA, and can verify that doing it on the floor of the bottom oven works nicely - I stretch the dough out on a lightly oiled teflon baking sheet and put it on the oven floor for about 10 minutes. This leaves the bottom crusty at the edges but with a nice chewy inside.</p>
						
					</div>
				</li>
				
