			<ul class="comment b2" id="comment-12317517">
				
				<li class="comment-author" >
                    
                        <div class="badges">
                            
                                



                            
                        </div>
                        <div class="profile" >
                            
                                

<img class="author-profile-picture" src="http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/discussion/avatars/2011/03/10/bluesnapper/27b4f362-8e83-42ce-802b-cd940926bddd/60x60.png" height="60" width="60" alt="" />
<a href="http://www.guardian.co.uk/discussion/user/bluesnapper" title="User profile page">bluesnapper</a>

                            
                            <p class="date">8 September 2011 9:31AM</p>
                        </div>
                    
					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>I tried making pizza from scratch a year or so ago and haven't eaten a shop-bought pizza since. I initially used Hugh F-W's dough recipe (probably from this website), but now I've got the hang of it I just do it by eye/feel.</p><p>Sure, it takes a while to knead dough and wait for it to rise, but once it's done it keeps in the fridge for a week or so and you can roll out a pizza whenever you feel like one. Which seems to be quite often when you've got the dough just sitting there! And, well, seeing as you've got the oven hot, why not have another one...or two? Not very filling these crispy-based pizzas!</p>
						
					</div>
				</li>
				
