                        </div>
                    
					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>I make pizzas when I make bread so it's a gorgeous thin sourdough base with just a hint of chew around the edges.  Agree with noodlesticks' tip on brushing the top with oil before the toppings - I quite like using garlic or chilli oil for doing that.</p><p>The other item you can stick in the oven to bake is a granite worktop saver (with the rubber feet removed) - Wilkie's do one for under £10.  I can get my oven to about 290C doing that and it makes the pizza (and the bread) so much crisper.</p><p>Topping-wise, I add tomato (with garlic/herbs), mozzarella, artichoke, pepper, capers and olives.</p>
						
					</div>
