                        <div class="profile" >
                            
                                

<img class="author-profile-picture" src="http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/discussion/avatars/2010/08/23/EllG/e5a4e909-5a5e-4914-a53a-e60b448905f2/60x60.png" height="60" width="60" alt="" />
<a href="http://www.guardian.co.uk/discussion/user/EllG" title="User profile page">EllG</a>

                            
                            <p class="date">8 September 2011 9:45AM</p>
                        </div>
                    
					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>Rocket, parma ham and parmesan, or italian sausage and rosemary.  Best two toppings for a pizza.  I will also accept ham but without pineapple (pineapple on pizza? Idiotic idea).</p><p>The dough is obviously key but the quality of your tomato sauce is also important. Doing home-made pizza and getting the sauce just right is tricky.  Too watery and it ruins the base, cheese and toppings; too thick and you just get stodge. And a mountain of oregano is good - you can't have too much.</p>
						
					</div>
				</li>
				
