			<ul class="comment b2" id="comment-12317840">
				
				<li class="comment-author" >
                    
                        <div class="badges">
                            
                                



                            
                        </div>
                        <div class="profile" >
                            
                                

<img class="author-profile-picture" src="http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/discussion/avatars/2010/11/10/Judes/b0f2d6c6-f55f-4c6f-92e5-e52ab8ce56b9/60x60.png" height="60" width="60" alt="" />
<a href="http://www.guardian.co.uk/discussion/user/Judes" title="User profile page">Judes</a>

                            
                            <p class="date">8 September 2011 9:50AM</p>
                        </div>
                    
					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>I'm lazy and I make the dough in the breadmaker using the 1.5 hour 'dough' setting. I use about 3 parts strong white bread flour to 1 part semolina which I've found makes the dough soft inside and crispy outside, even when eating the leftovers the following day (sorry Italians!). One of my favourite toppings (completely unauthentic) is pesto spread on the dough and topped with sliced red onion and fennel which has been tossed in olive oil and black pepper. Much quicker than cooking down a tin of tomatoes for the topping! I also hardly ever put cheese on top. Last time I used mozzerella it oozed liquid all over the place and made the base soggy.</p>
						
					</div>
				</li>
				
