			<ul class="comment b2" id="comment-12317863">
				
				<li class="comment-author" >
                    
                        <div class="badges">
                            
                                



                            
                        </div>
                        <div class="profile" >
                            
                                

<img class="author-profile-picture" src="http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/discussion/avatars/2010/09/02/cta_262190_13/1cfba3f0-2fd4-488b-949f-ae4f835c3c24/60x60.png" height="60" width="60" alt="" />
<a href="http://www.guardian.co.uk/discussion/user/bluebellnutter" title="User profile page">bluebellnutter</a>

                            
                            <p class="date">8 September 2011 9:52AM</p>
                        </div>
                    
					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>Having spent my entire HCSE tech project making pizzas, I've become rather fussy about them.</p><p>The base has to be soft, if it's thin and crispy I don't want it. Not too thick but definitely soft. </p><p>The sauce has to be quite thick. Not so thick it doesn't move when prodded like most supermarket pizzas but "gloopy". There also has to eb plenty of garlic in there, but that's a purely personal preference.</p><p>There has to be plenty of cheese. If something is meant to have cheese on it it needs to be cheesy.</p><p>I prefer a meat topping, pepperoni and ham being the best.</p>
						
					</div>
				</li>
				
