                        </div>
                    
					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>I always make my own pizza from scratch. I use Nigella's dough recipe - I have altered the timings slightly for my oven. It has a lovely texture cause of the olive oils added to the dough - crunchy on the outside. I prove it in my airing cupboard with cling film and a tea towel on top of the bowl. I put Sainsburys premium chopped toms on top and mix in some dried Italian herbs. I use pepperoni or chorizo as a topping plus olives and mushrooms. Sometimes I add an egg in the middle, some pineapple. For cheese, I use a combination of cheddar low fat mozzarella and fresh parmesan. Make sure you invest in a decent pizza baking tray from John Lewis or equivalent quality - TK Maxx is good for quality bakeware.</p>
						
					</div>
				</li>
				
